title: Elizabeth Warren Raised $24.6 Million in Third Quarter
text:
Elizabeth Warren said she raised $24.6 million for her Democratic presidential bid from July to September, a period that coincided with the Massachusetts senator’s growing crowds and rise in many national and early primary state polls.

Ms. Warren continued her upward fundraising trajectory—from $6 million in the first quarter to $19.2 million in the second—although Vermont Sen. Bernie Sanders raised slightly more than she did in the most recent three-month period, $25.3 million, his campaign said.
